          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJrC2hB7hpcM6Q2SKSnFpGHX1BhsnIKpVULHfrbAMM25CDhVcie=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100",
          "description": "Worst service, even the elderly customers were complaining about the Caucasian male older and the middle age Indian worker opening up cases for people.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2tkaFNEVnNUbnBWYW5nNFNYTXhOMlJPY0drMFpYYxAB!2m1!1s0x0:0xf850a415c7c97547!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOkdhSDVsTnpVang4SXMxN2ROcGk0ZXc%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "3 months ago",
          "date_iso8601": "2026-03-03T20:49:11+00:00"
        },
        {
          "username": "Elinor Garely",
          "rating": 1,
          "contributor_id": "116118320758440131893",
          "user_review_count": 33,
          "user_photo_count": 10,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKqXJiw4zfxePoLEyUjiiWNi-SGflGPirjygbbdZ7wY4W2lVhxf=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100",
          "description": "It\u2019s deeply disappointing that a company the size of DR shows such disregard for its customers. As the only multi-service pharmacy in the neighborhood, it benefits from a captive audience\u2014but instead of rising to the occasion, it settles for being the default. This location could be a trusted, go-to retailer if it hired staff who understood the meaning of customer service and treated patrons with respect.\nShelves are frequently empty or poorly stocked, with essential products missing. Requests for assistance are met with indifference, and customer service is limited to a few overburdened cashiers who appear to be totally uninterested in their job and responsibilities. Shoplifters are visibly active and ignored. On multiple occasions, I\u2019ve felt unsafe due to individuals wandering the aisles unchecked. Reporting these concerns to staff is futile\u2014they\u2019re dismissive and uninterested.\nThis store operates with minimal effort and maximum disregard. If there were other options nearby, I would not choose this location. DR needs to take responsibility for its environment, its staffing, and its role in the community.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSURIanByN2tRRRAB!2m1!1s0x0:0xf850a415c7c97547!3m1!1s2@1:CIHM0ogKEICAgIDHjpr7kQE%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "Edited 8 months ago",
          "date_iso8601": "2025-10-23T14:37:27+00:00"
        },
        {
          "username": "Leena Kaur",
          "rating": 1,
          "contributor_id": "105286061414939475414",
          "user_review_count": 56,
          "user_photo_count": 14,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKbM-pRurLqLIEAhMUGdDVwtekQxKSwHDBrYelbRyO6ymjTXw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100",
          "description": "THE ABSOLUTE MOST INCOMPETRNT AND LAZY PHARMACY DEPT! Rude and selfish and I\u2019m still on hold for over 12 minutes and just had a medical procedure and need to fill a prescription asap. But pharmacist and their \u201ctechs\u201d are slow, incompetent and it\u2019s now almost 15 min and I\u2019m still on hold. Maybe if they spent less time on their personal cell phones , they may help someone. I keep waiting to post this review in the event they take me off hold but no. I\u2019m still on hold and it\u2019s better to acknowledge the severely low rating of this worthless place!",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sChdDSUhNMG9nS0VLdkc3YXZNM1BiSDJRRRAB!2m1!1s0x0:0xf850a415c7c97547!3m1!1s2@1:CIHM0ogKEKvG7avM3PbH2QE%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "a year ago",
          "date_iso8601": "2025-05-19T15:33:45+00:00"
        },
        {
          "username": "J F",
          "rating": 1,
          "contributor_id": "107055232792314957414",
          "user_review_count": 142,
          "user_photo_count": 42,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKVLnqu7WSX8yTTxh_uyOq2FTVnkbc_5lOMRNv0FzgZzEt2=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100",
          "description": "Minor headache sent me to this Duane Reade to pick up a bottle of Tylenol.  All Pain meds are now locked up, but there are convenient buttons to press in the isle to get custom care people to unlock the plastic panels.  10 minutes worth of pressing the buttons escalated the minor headache to severe.  A Susan walked over with a very unhappy \"why are you bothering me\" face.  Now my headache is 9 out of 10.\nI shared with the cashier my thoughts on the experience.  His stoned face looked past me.  I repeated my comments, and he asked \"would that be all?\"\nNow it is full-blown migraine.\nI applaud (and hopeful of) Private Equity taking over Walgreen and splitting up its inefficient businesses, either make it go away or run more like a business, hopefully without the Susan or stoned cashier type.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUR2X016T2NREAE!2m1!1s0x0:0xf850a415c7c97547!3m1!1s2@1:CIHM0ogKEICAgIDv_MzOcQ%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "a year ago",
          "date_iso8601": "2024-12-18T16:19:50+00:00"
        }
